1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:11,533
<i> Dizon, behind you!</i>

2
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:15,567
<i> They got Monty.</i>

3
00:00:15,700 --> 00:00:17,067
<i> We need to get him back.</i>

4
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:18,433
<i> There are too many of them.</i>

5
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:22,200
<i>Then I heard from Faye earlier
that father is going to announce</i>

6
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,767
<i>that I am her daughter here
at the party.</i>

7
00:00:23,900 --> 00:00:25,667
<i>Why? Don't you want
to be introduced?</i>

8
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,933
<i>- I don't know.
-Have you talked to your father?</i>

9
00:00:28,067 --> 00:00:29,000
<i> Bobby!</i>

10
00:00:29,133 --> 00:00:30,733
<i>- Have you seen daddy?
- No, not really.</i>

11
00:00:30,867 --> 00:00:31,733
<i> Daddy is something else</i>

12
00:00:31,867 --> 00:00:33,800
<i>just when he's needed
in the program.</i>

13
00:00:33,967 --> 00:00:35,933
<i> What are you doing here, Glen?</i>

14
00:00:36,067 --> 00:00:37,500
<i>- How is Dizon?
- He's okay.</i>

15
00:00:37,633 --> 00:00:38,767
<i> The injury isn't serious.</i>

16
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,500
<i>What's the latest update
on Monty?</i>

17
00:00:40,633 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>Whoever's in charge of Monty
seems to be a big shot.</i>

18
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,733
<i>- Kneel!
- Boss, what is this?</i>

19
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:45,867
<i> Boss, what does this mean?</i>

20
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:46,800
<i>Boss, what are you going to do?</i>

21
00:00:46,933 --> 00:00:48,733
<i>You know what I hate most,
Monty?</i>

22
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,167
<i>Someone who threatens me
who would talk</i>

23
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,067
<i>because he didn't get
what he wanted.</i>

24
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,767
<i> Boss, I really won't do that.</i>

25
00:00:54,900 --> 00:00:56,467
<i> Boss, we'll take care of this.</i>

26
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:57,733
<i> You idiot!</i>

27
00:00:57,867 --> 00:01:00,833
<i>Chop it up and throw it
in different parts of the river!</i>

28
00:01:02,033 --> 00:01:03,000
<i> Is there a problem?</i>

29
00:01:03,133 --> 00:01:04,600
<i> Nothing. Just fix that.</i>

30
00:01:04,733 --> 00:01:05,667
<i> Hello, Father?</i>

31
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:08,067
<i>I'm here at the abandoned
warehouse.</i>

32
00:01:16,133 --> 00:01:17,533
Mommy.

33
00:01:17,667 --> 00:01:18,900
Hey, Faye.

34
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:20,767
Did you find your daddy?

35
00:01:20,900 --> 00:01:22,133
Not yet.

36
00:01:22,267 --> 00:01:25,000
And I couldn't
find Glend, either.

37
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:26,867
Bobby is looking for them, too.

38
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,467
Faye, please.

39
00:01:28,600 --> 00:01:32,267
Do not mention that girl's name
in front of me.

40
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,467
She's not part of our family.

41
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Madam...

42
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:43,933
The guests
are getting impatient.

43
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,833
What are we going to do, Madam?

44
00:01:45,967 --> 00:01:48,233
You know, let's start
the program.

45
00:01:48,367 --> 00:01:51,133
Just call Joaquin on stage.

46
00:01:51,267 --> 00:01:53,100
I'm sure he's just
there somewhere.

47
00:01:53,233 --> 00:01:55,900
He'll come forward
if he is called.

48
00:01:56,033 --> 00:01:57,267
Okay, thank you.

49
00:01:58,900 --> 00:02:00,500
Joaquin, where are you?

50
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:10,100
Hello, Father?

51
00:02:10,233 --> 00:02:11,667
Where are you?

52
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,567
Faye has been looking for you
for a while now.

53
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:16,367
The program is about to start.

54
00:02:16,533 --> 00:02:19,233
Bobby, Bobby, listen carefully.

55
00:02:19,367 --> 00:02:20,633
What's that, Father?

56
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:23,067
I can't hear you that well,
the line is choppy.

57
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:32,067
Bobby, Glen killed the seller
of pimple patches.

58
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,167
He is the mastermind.

59
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,133
- Hello?
- Good Evening, everyone!

60
00:02:37,267 --> 00:02:38,700
Has everyone eaten already?

61
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:42,300
Was the food prepared
by Mayor delicious?

62
00:02:42,433 --> 00:02:43,500
Did you enjoy?

63
00:02:43,633 --> 00:02:44,500
Yes!

64
00:02:44,633 --> 00:02:46,500
That's good!

65
00:02:46,633 --> 00:02:49,933
Wait a second,
I'll just look for a signal.

66
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:51,300
Just wait.
I'll just go out.

67
00:02:51,433 --> 00:02:53,933
And at this point, let me
introduce here on stage

68
00:02:54,067 --> 00:03:02,167
our dearest and beloved Mayor,
Joaquin "El Hepe" Guerero!

69
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,533
Bobby!

70
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,133
Can you hear me?

71
00:03:56,467 --> 00:03:58,567
Hello, Father?

72
00:03:58,700 --> 00:03:59,767
Hello?

73
00:04:03,767 --> 00:04:05,600
What are you doing here?

74
00:04:05,733 --> 00:04:07,067
What are you doing here?

75
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,233
Let go of me.

76
00:04:11,367 --> 00:04:12,967
You're a demon!

77
00:04:13,100 --> 00:04:14,700
Me?

78
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:16,067
I'm a demon?

79
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:17,267
Yes!

80
00:04:19,033 --> 00:04:21,700
I saw everything, Glen.

81
00:04:21,833 --> 00:04:23,900
I saw everything you did!

82
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:32,067
And I don't know how I raised
a monster like you!

83
00:04:38,633 --> 00:04:40,567
Hidalgo Street.

84
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:42,267
That's near here.

85
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:55,267
You don't know?

86
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:57,967
Are you sure you don't know?

87
00:04:58,100 --> 00:05:00,233
You made me this way!

88
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,700
It's because of you!

89
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:05,767
I have no son who kills people!

90
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,867
You're always like that.

91
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:15,367
All you see are my mistakes.

92
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,767
No matter what I do,

93
00:05:18,667 --> 00:05:20,700
no matter what achievements
I get,

94
00:05:20,833 --> 00:05:22,167
no matter what I have reached,

95
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,067
it was never enough for you!

96
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:29,033
I was never enough for you!

97
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:33,367
I will make sure
that you will rot in hell!

98
00:05:37,900 --> 00:05:42,233
You just don't know
all the things I did for you!

99
00:05:45,533 --> 00:05:50,300
I ruined Godfather Victor's name
so you'd win the election!

100
00:05:50,433 --> 00:05:53,667
I handed you that position
on a silver platter!

101
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:56,200
You should thank me!

102
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:58,567
You're a devil!

103
00:05:58,700 --> 00:06:01,267
I don't have a son
who is a devil!

104
00:06:03,067 --> 00:06:04,500
You're an animal!

105
00:06:12,567 --> 00:06:13,833
Dad?

106
00:06:16,200 --> 00:06:17,100
Dad...

107
00:06:26,867 --> 00:06:27,800
Dad?

108
00:06:53,933 --> 00:06:56,633
Mister, can I ask you
a question?

109
00:06:56,767 --> 00:06:57,833
What is it?

110
00:06:57,967 --> 00:07:01,133
Is there an abandoned warehouse
here on Hidalgo Street?

111
00:07:01,267 --> 00:07:02,367
I don't think there is.

112
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:03,533
There are just houses here.

113
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,700
Or maybe you're looking
for a different Hidalgo Street.

114
00:07:07,833 --> 00:07:09,833
Is there another Hidalgo
Street aside from this?

115
00:07:09,967 --> 00:07:12,367
Yes, there's an extension.

116
00:07:12,500 --> 00:07:13,833
Maybe that's where the warehouse
you're looking for.

117
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,400
Where is that?

118
00:07:15,533 --> 00:07:17,500
Just go straight, first corner,
make a right.

119
00:07:17,633 --> 00:07:18,700
Go straight, first corner,
make a right.

120
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:19,900
Okay, thank you.

121
00:07:20,033 --> 00:07:20,967
- Okay, fine.
- Thank you.

122
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,100
Dad...

123
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,133
Dad, you need this.

124
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:36,533
Dad?

125
00:07:36,667 --> 00:07:37,933
What now, Dad?

126
00:07:38,067 --> 00:07:39,833
You need to drink this, Dad?

127
00:07:39,967 --> 00:07:41,933
- Give it to me.
- Dad.

128
00:07:47,433 --> 00:07:49,100
- Get it.
- Give it to me.

129
00:08:03,100 --> 00:08:04,633
I need that.

130
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:08,167
Go ahead and crawl.

131
00:08:42,833 --> 00:08:46,700
<i>From now on, don't meddle
with my plans!</i>

132
00:08:46,833 --> 00:08:48,300
<i>We have to do something
about this.</i>

133
00:08:48,433 --> 00:08:49,833
<i> What do you want me to do?</i>

134
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:51,767
<i>Ask for forgiveness
from Victor?</i>

135
00:08:54,900 --> 00:08:56,200
Goodbye, Dad.

136
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,733
Goodbye.

137
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:08,933
Checka...

138
00:09:09,067 --> 00:09:10,900
Where is Joaquin?

139
00:09:11,033 --> 00:09:12,600
I don't know, Madam.

140
00:09:12,733 --> 00:09:16,067
But I've been looking around
for a while now.

141
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,933
I still haven't seen him.

142
00:09:18,067 --> 00:09:21,833
But I think Bobby knows
where he is.

143
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:23,567
Bobby? Why Bobby?

144
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:26,900
Well, earlier, I saw Bobby
was talking to the Mayor

145
00:09:27,033 --> 00:09:28,167
on the phone.

146
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:31,033
Then look now,
she's gone, right?

147
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:32,767
She left.

148
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:35,867
Bobby has been
looking for daddy.

149
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:37,800
Where did she go?

150
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:40,833
Well, Madam, I wasn't able
to follow her,

151
00:09:40,967 --> 00:09:44,233
but she must have something
to do with it.

152
00:09:44,367 --> 00:09:45,800
My apologies,
ladies and gentlemen,

153
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:49,600
but the Mayor still seems shy.

154
00:09:49,733 --> 00:09:50,900
Why don't we go out?

155
00:09:51,033 --> 00:09:55,367
Right? So the Mayor can get
more excited to come out?

156
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,433
Mayor, we've been waiting
for you!

157
00:09:58,567 --> 00:10:01,367
Don't be shy anymore!
Don't hide anymore!

158
00:10:01,533 --> 00:10:03,467
We know, even though
you're getting older,

159
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:06,967
we love the Mayor very much!

160
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:13,567
Let's call here on stage
our beloved mayor,

161
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:18,600
Mayor Joaquin "El Hepe"
Guerrero!

162
00:10:25,567 --> 00:10:26,433
Boss, it's okay.

163
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:28,700
We've disposed of
Monty's body properly.

164
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:34,300
That's the Mayor, right?

165
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:35,733
What happened, Boss?

166
00:10:35,867 --> 00:10:36,833
I don't know with him.

167
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:39,600
I think he had stroke.

168
00:10:39,733 --> 00:10:41,233
Is your father already dead,
Boss?

169
00:10:45,033 --> 00:10:46,967
What do you think, Dante?

170
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:49,733
You're really stupid,
aren't you?

171
00:10:49,867 --> 00:10:50,967
Look at him.

172
00:10:51,100 --> 00:10:53,067
Is he still breathing?

173
00:10:53,200 --> 00:10:54,500
Aren't we going to bury him yet?

174
00:10:54,633 --> 00:10:56,933
Let's dispose him.

175
00:10:57,067 --> 00:10:59,333
No, we can't.

176
00:10:59,467 --> 00:11:02,167
That's going to cause
a big mess here.

177
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,100
I'm taking him to the hospital

178
00:11:04,233 --> 00:11:07,067
so he can be declared
dead on arrival.

179
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,667
Do you understand?

180
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:15,333
And make sure Monty's body
is properly disposed of, okay?

181
00:11:15,467 --> 00:11:19,400
The police might have an
investigation here,

182
00:11:19,867 --> 00:11:21,533
and we'll get caught.

183
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:26,867
What are you waiting for?

184
00:11:43,100 --> 00:11:44,300
What, Faye?

185
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:46,800
You still haven't seen
your daddy?

186
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:48,533
Not yet.

187
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:53,300
I've asked everyone
while giving out giveaways,

188
00:11:53,433 --> 00:11:56,200
but no one really knows
where your daddy is.

189
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:57,933
Thanks, Jade.

190
00:11:58,067 --> 00:12:00,033
I don't really know
what's going on anymore.

191
00:12:02,033 --> 00:12:03,033
Faye!

192
00:12:03,167 --> 00:12:04,267
Vince, what?

193
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,667
Have you seen daddy?

194
00:12:05,800 --> 00:12:10,600
No, but we won't stop looking
because I'm sure he's around.

195
00:12:10,733 --> 00:12:11,600
I hope so.

196
00:12:11,733 --> 00:12:13,167
And, I already talked to
the head of security

197
00:12:13,300 --> 00:12:14,567
at the events venue.

198
00:12:14,733 --> 00:12:17,400
But they don't know
where the Mayor went.

199
00:12:17,533 --> 00:12:18,700
Thanks for the effort, okay?

200
00:12:18,833 --> 00:12:20,233
But don't worry.

201
00:12:20,367 --> 00:12:21,300
I'm leaving now.

202
00:12:21,433 --> 00:12:23,500
I'll also ask around
at the nearby precincts.

203
00:12:23,633 --> 00:12:24,533
Okay, okay.

204
00:12:24,667 --> 00:12:26,000
I also need to talk to mommy

205
00:12:26,133 --> 00:12:27,867
because daddy might have
an emergency meeting

206
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,467
that I don't know about,
because Glen is not here either.

207
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:33,100
Okay, Faye,
I'll go first, okay?

208
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:34,467
Vince, you take care of Faye.

209
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:35,233
Okay, man.

210
00:12:35,367 --> 00:12:36,567
Thanks, okay?

211
00:12:38,933 --> 00:12:39,967
Let's go, Jade.

212
00:12:41,700 --> 00:12:42,633
Oh no!

213
00:12:42,767 --> 00:12:44,367
Something like that
breaking is a bad omen.

214
00:12:44,500 --> 00:12:46,833
What did you say?

215
00:12:46,967 --> 00:12:50,100
Something like that
breaking is a bad omen.

216
00:12:50,267 --> 00:12:52,633
Don't say that!

217
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:53,767
Sorry, Faye!

218
00:13:05,367 --> 00:13:07,867
You really had to do that, Dad?

219
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,867
You really don't trust me.

220
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,933
You really followed me, right?

221
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,300
And now...

222
00:13:28,367 --> 00:13:29,733
you're going to die...

223
00:13:31,367 --> 00:13:32,967
and it's your fault.

224
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,400
It's your fault!

225
00:13:39,733 --> 00:13:41,100
Bobby?

226
00:13:41,233 --> 00:13:42,967
Glen!

227
00:13:43,100 --> 00:13:45,100
They've been looking for you
at the party for some time now.

228
00:13:45,233 --> 00:13:46,600
Where is father?

229
00:13:46,733 --> 00:13:48,267
Good thing I saw you.

230
00:13:48,400 --> 00:13:49,667
I need your help.

231
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:51,067
Something happened to daddy.

232
00:13:51,200 --> 00:13:52,300
What's the problem?

233
00:13:52,433 --> 00:13:53,533
He's here.

234
00:13:53,667 --> 00:13:56,000
We were just talking earlier,
but he suddenly collapsed.

235
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:02,567
Let's take him
to the hospital, quick!

236
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:03,367
Okay.

237
00:14:05,167 --> 00:14:06,667
Father...

238
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,867
Father...

239
00:14:13,533 --> 00:14:15,400
If that Bobby
has anything to do

240
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,067
with your father's
disappearance,

241
00:14:17,200 --> 00:14:19,467
that girl will definitely
hear from me!

242
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:21,867
Mommy, what will
Bobby do to daddy?

243
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,633
I don't know!

244
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:28,433
But it's obvious that
she has her own personal agenda.

245
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:30,867
Mommy, I understand
how you feel,

246
00:14:31,000 --> 00:14:34,833
but is it okay if we give Bobby
a chance first?

247
00:14:34,967 --> 00:14:37,300
She's not doing anything wrong.

248
00:14:39,033 --> 00:14:40,500
It's your brother.

249
00:14:40,633 --> 00:14:42,433
Glen, where are you?

250
00:14:42,567 --> 00:14:44,867
We have been
looking for you for a while!

251
00:14:47,867 --> 00:14:49,600
What?

252
00:14:49,733 --> 00:14:51,533
Oh my god!

253
00:14:51,667 --> 00:14:53,267
Okay, Mom.

254
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:54,233
See you at the hospital.

255
00:14:56,567 --> 00:14:57,733
Doesn't he have maintenance
medicines, Glen?

256
00:14:57,867 --> 00:15:01,567
Or any medicine he can take
to prevent this from happening?

257
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:04,300
I tried to find it.

258
00:15:04,433 --> 00:15:06,367
Bobby, I was also confused.

259
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:09,300
When I found him,
he wasn't responding anymore?

260
00:15:11,933 --> 00:15:13,400
Dad, we're almost
at the hospital.

261
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,100
- What happened?
- Faye! Faye!

262
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:26,533
Your daddy had a stroke!

263
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:29,267
Glen and your dad are on their
way to the hospital now.

264
00:15:29,400 --> 00:15:31,700
Madam, the visitors
are asking questions.

265
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:32,833
They're getting bored.

266
00:15:32,967 --> 00:15:35,533
Cheka! Cheka, take care
of the visitors first.

267
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:36,833
I need to go to the hospital.

268
00:15:36,967 --> 00:15:38,500
- Why? What happened?
- We need to go.

269
00:15:38,633 --> 00:15:40,300
Joaquin had a stroke!

270
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:41,333
- What?
- Yes! But please

271
00:15:41,467 --> 00:15:45,033
just tell them
that he just felt ill, okay?

272
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,200
Oh, okay.

273
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:47,067
We're going to the hospital now.

274
00:15:47,200 --> 00:15:48,967
- Okay, Ma'am.
- Faye, come on.

275
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,133
Oh my.

276
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:05,667
You talked to father,
that's why you found us?

277
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:07,067
He called earlier.

278
00:16:10,033 --> 00:16:11,433
What did he say?

279
00:16:11,567 --> 00:16:12,500
I don't understand.

280
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:14,867
The signal is weak inside.

281
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:17,967
Glen, why did you go there?

282
00:16:18,100 --> 00:16:20,533
What's in there?

283
00:16:20,667 --> 00:16:21,533
We just went to get some air.

284
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:25,200
We talked about his legacy.

285
00:16:28,067 --> 00:16:30,367
I wonder why dad called?

286
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:35,067
We talked about the projects
you could help with.

287
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,600
He has so many projects
for Calabari.

288
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:40,033
They were great.

289
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:41,767
It's not too late, Glen.

290
00:16:41,933 --> 00:16:43,633
Father is still breathing.

291
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:01,567
Hot, hot, hot.

292
00:17:08,467 --> 00:17:09,200
Sorry, sorry!

293
00:17:09,333 --> 00:17:10,367
It's an emergency!

294
00:17:12,133 --> 00:17:13,233
It's too hot.

295
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:18,067
What happened to you?

296
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,300
Let me guess. You're being
stupid again, aren't you?

297
00:17:20,433 --> 00:17:22,433
The nurse was in a hurry,
and I bumped into her.

298
00:17:22,567 --> 00:17:24,733
It's not my fault.

299
00:17:24,867 --> 00:17:26,833
You, you're an addition
to my bad luck here.

300
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:28,733
Why are you here?

301
00:17:28,867 --> 00:17:32,100
I watched over Sir Tonyo.

302
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:33,867
Tonyo is lucky,

303
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:36,667
there are many people
taking care of him.

304
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:40,633
Me, I've been through it all,
and still nothing.

305
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:42,033
Do you know why?

306
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:43,933
Sir Tonyo is kind.

307
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:46,800
While you, you have
a bad attitude.

308
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:49,800
You know, the heat of the coffee
just went through my head.

309
00:17:49,967 --> 00:17:51,533
Can you leave now?

310
00:17:51,667 --> 00:17:53,567
You're adding to this.

311
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,667
Grumpy.

312
00:17:55,800 --> 00:17:57,500
Even my groin.

313
00:17:59,067 --> 00:18:00,067
Here!

314
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,067
Return that to me.

315
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:07,300
Wash it!

316
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:16,200
Her style is old.

317
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:17,400
Wash it...

318
00:18:17,533 --> 00:18:19,733
Then I'll return it to you.

319
00:18:19,867 --> 00:18:21,667
This happened during
Tandang Sora's time.

320
00:18:23,500 --> 00:18:25,067
I knew it,

321
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:27,400
even back in Switzerland,
you already had a crush on me.

322
00:18:44,167 --> 00:18:45,833
Father...

323
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,533
Fight, Father.

324
00:19:11,067 --> 00:19:12,933
Nurse! Nurse,
where's my husband?

325
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:14,500
This way, Madam.

326
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,033
Glen!

327
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,367
Glen, what happened?

328
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:20,733
Mom, we were just talking,
then he suddenly had an attack.

329
00:19:20,867 --> 00:19:22,500
Daddy, Daddy? How's daddy?

330
00:19:22,633 --> 00:19:24,200
They're doing everything, Faye.

331
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,433
They're doing everything.

332
00:19:25,567 --> 00:19:27,667
What are you doing here?

333
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,267
You're not part of the family!

334
00:19:29,433 --> 00:19:30,733
Go away!

335
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,500
Mommy, Mommy, this is not
the right time.

336
00:19:32,633 --> 00:19:33,500
What do you mean, this is not

337
00:19:33,633 --> 00:19:36,900
- the right time?
- Faye, Faye, it's okay.

338
00:19:37,033 --> 00:19:38,633
- Maybe, I''ll just go...
- Go away, go away.

339
00:19:38,767 --> 00:19:39,967
Glen...

340
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:40,800
I'll go ahead.

341
00:19:49,900 --> 00:19:51,067
Joaquin...

342
00:20:02,733 --> 00:20:04,467
Glen?

343
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,500
I came as soon as I heard.

344
00:20:23,233 --> 00:20:24,700
Joaquin...

345
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:29,100
It's good, Jun, I'll be
discharged tomorrow, Doc said.

346
00:20:29,233 --> 00:20:31,833
Well, I'm bored as hell here.

347
00:20:31,967 --> 00:20:34,233
-Thank goodness I can go back...
-Boss, boss...

348
00:20:34,367 --> 00:20:35,567
Boss...

349
00:20:35,733 --> 00:20:37,100
What are you doing here?

350
00:20:37,233 --> 00:20:39,333
Boss, the Mayor was rushed
to the hospital.

351
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:40,933
What?

352
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,633
Why? What happened?

353
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:45,300
Boss, I heard he had a stroke.

354
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,733
<i>You knew that your mother
was abandoned</i>

355
00:21:04,867 --> 00:21:07,067
<i>by the man who got her pregnant?</i>

356
00:21:09,467 --> 00:21:12,700
<i> Yes, Grandmother. Why?</i>

357
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:16,467
<i>Because the one who got her
pregnant was Mayor Guerrero!</i>

358
00:21:16,600 --> 00:21:19,900
<i>At that time, I would have
left everything for her,</i>

359
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:22,233
<i> including my wife, Sophia.</i>

360
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:26,000
<i>One day, she suddenly stopped
getting in touch with me.</i>

361
00:21:26,133 --> 00:21:28,267
<i> Do you still call me Mayor?</i>

362
00:21:30,533 --> 00:21:32,233
<i> Never mind.</i>

363
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:34,433
<i> I can wait.</i>

364
00:21:34,567 --> 00:21:39,133
<i>And when that day comes,
I'm sure I'll be very happy.</i>

365
00:21:39,267 --> 00:21:41,233
<i> Has daddy told you yet?</i>

366
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:42,367
<i> Which one?</i>

367
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,000
<i>He's planning to announce
at the party later</i>

368
00:21:44,133 --> 00:21:45,233
<i> that you're his daughter.</i>

369
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,233
<i> Father...</i>

370
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:52,633
<i> You mean you're accepting me?</i>

371
00:21:52,767 --> 00:21:55,800
<i> Yes, Father.</i>

372
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:57,600
<i>Thank you very much,
my daughter.</i>

373
00:22:45,267 --> 00:22:48,267
Tonyo, it's Father.

374
00:23:20,867 --> 00:23:22,433
When the doctors revive him,

375
00:23:22,600 --> 00:23:23,800
I need you to do something
for me.

376
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:25,700
Are you seriously
asking me this?

377
00:23:25,833 --> 00:23:27,733
We're talking about your dad!

378
00:23:27,867 --> 00:23:30,000
What was the last thing you
and my husband talked about?

379
00:23:30,133 --> 00:23:32,833
And why didn't you tell anyone
you were going to see him?

380
00:23:32,967 --> 00:23:35,467
Ma'am, I don't know.
He just called me.

381
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:37,833
When I got there,
he and Glen were together.

382
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:39,867
Why are you bringing Glen here?

383
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,267
Zondra!

384
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:44,333
Mother!

385
00:23:44,467 --> 00:23:46,300
Mother, don't leave me!

386
00:23:46,433 --> 00:23:48,167
What are you thinking,
my grandchild?

387
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:51,700
I hope he shows himself to me.

388
00:23:51,833 --> 00:23:54,400
Oh, well, we know someone,
a psychic.

389
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:56,000
It's Madam Alma.

390
00:23:56,167 --> 00:23:57,833
Are you ready, Ma'am?
